Abdo G. ASKER d/b/a Premier Meat Market, Appellant, v. Kenneth B. STEPHENS et al., Appellees. No. 25313. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. May 20, 1968. Daniel R. Coffman, Jr., Jacksonville, Fla., for appellant. Victor E. Raymos, Jacksonville, Fla., for appellees. Carin Ann Clauss, Atty., Dept. of Labor, Washington, D. C., amicus curiae.

Before POPE,* TUTTLE and CLAYTON, Circuit Judges.

Of the Ninth Circuit, sitting by designation.

 PER CURIAM:

The judgment of the trial court was, in all respects, correct. It is therefore,

Affirmed.
